                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d404">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.51W89 France/682: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in France (<persName corresp="#p_AN1" type="to"
                        >Armour</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-06-07T12:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 7, 1932—noon</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>213. British and Italian [representatives?] signed <persName corresp="#p_HH1"
                        >Hoover</persName> year debt postponement agreement Saturday.<note n="43"
                        xml:id="d404fn43">June 4.</note> Treasury feels that it must within a very
                    short time request French payment due June 15th unless French agreement can be
                    completed at once.</p>
                <p>Department assumes you are pressing this matter in every feasible manner. Please
                    report by wire.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SHL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
